course_title: Neonatal Nurse Practitioner Clinical Practicum II
course_description: This course will provide a clinical practice preceptorship with faculty oversight to develop skills in health assessment and physical exam, differential diagnosis, diagnostic reasoning and plan of care for neonates and infants/toddlers in acute and critical care settings.
prerequisites: NRSG 609 or equivalent transfer credit as prerequisite.
